Why Binary Search Works?

Suppose

nums[mid] < nums[mid+1]
1 3 5 7
      ↑

The array is increasing.

A peak cannot be on the left, because values are still rising.

Move right.

Suppose

nums[mid] > nums[mid+1]
7 5 4 2
↑

The array is decreasing.

A peak already exists on the left (possibly mid).

Move left.

