Interview Summary
Approach	Time	Space
Brute Force (Check Every Element)	O(n)	O(1)
Better (Find Maximum Element)	O(n)	O(1)
Binary Search (Optimal)	O(log n)	O(1)
Key Trick

Instead of checking both neighbors every time, compare only:

nums[mid]

with

nums[mid + 1]
If the slope is increasing → Move Right
If the slope is decreasing → Move Left

Eventually,

low == high

which is guaranteed to be a peak element.

Pattern
Array
   ↓
Pick mid
   ↓
nums[mid] < nums[mid+1] ?
      ↓
   Yes        No
    ↓          ↓
Move Right  Move Left (including mid)
      ↓
low == high
      ↓
Peak Found
